ell Friends School alumni]]\n[[Category:Transatlantic flight]]\n[[Category:United States Air Force officers]]\n[[Category:United States airmail pilots]]\n[[Category:United States Army Air Forces officers]]\n[[Category:United States Army Medal of Honor recipients]]\n[[Category:University of Wisconsin\u2013Madison College of Engineering alumni]]\n[[Category:Writers from Detroit]]\n", "name_user": "2600:1003:b019:71d6:197f:26fb:5f88:c7c0", "label": "unsafe", "comment": "(Added info)", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Charles_Lindbergh"}
{"title_page": "David M. Thomas Jr.", "text_new": "{{Other uses|David Thomas (disambiguation){{!}}David Thomas}}\n{{Infobox military person\n | name         = David M. Thomas\n | image        = Admiral David Thomas valedictory picture.jpg\n | caption      =\n | birth_date         =\n | death_date         =\n | birth_place =\n | death_place =\n | nickname     =\n | allegiance   =\n | branch       = {{navy|United States}}\n | serviceyears =\n | rank         = [[Rear admiral (United States)|Rear Admiral]]\n | unit         =\n | commands     = [[JTF-GTMO]]<br />[[Carrier Strike Group Two]]<br />[[Commander, Naval Surface Forces Atlantic|Naval Surface Forces Atlantic]]\n | battles      =\n | awards       =\n | relations    =\n | laterwork    =\n}}\n[[File:David Thomas salutes -- cropped.jpg|thumb|David M. Thomas salutes as he takes command of JTF-GTMO.]]\n'''David M. Thomas''' was an officer in the [[United States Navy]].<ref name=MiamiHerald20080528>\n{{cite news\n |url=http://www.miamiherald.com/519/story/548860.html \n |title='9/11 hero' takes over prison camp \n |publisher=[[Miami Herald]] \n |author=Carol Rosenberg \n |date=May 28, 2008 \n |accessdate=2008-05-28 \n |url-status=bot: unknown \n |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/5Y9hNfI8s?url=http://www.miamiherald.com/519/story/548860.html \n |archivedate=May 28, 2008 \n|author-link=Carol Rosenberg \n }}\n\n</ref>\n\n==Early life==\nThomas's father was a career Navy officer.<ref name=MiamiHeraldAboutThomas20080528>\n{{cite news\n |url=http://www.miamiherald.com/1060/story/549245.html \n |title=About Navy Rear Adm. David M. Thomas \n |publisher=[[Miami Herald]] \n |date=May 28, 2008 \n |accessdate=2008-05-28 \n |url-status=bot: unknown \n |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/5Y9dbVVUQ?url=http://www.miamiherald.com/1060/story/549245.html \n |archivedate=May 28, 2008 \n}}\n\n</ref>\nThomas, and three of his brothers, are graduates of the [[United States Naval Academy]]. All are retired, including one who was in the Marine Corps. Another brother served in the Peace Corps. His two uncles also were Navy officers via Officers' Candidate School programs. \nThomas graduated in 1981.\n\nThomas was a 1976 graduate of [[Thomas Sprigg Wootton High School]] in Rockville, Maryland.\n\n==Navy career==\nIn 1999, Thomas commanded the [[destroyer]] [[USS Ross (DDG-71)|USS ''Ross'']].<ref name=MiamiHeraldAboutThomas20080528/>  \nHe has served aboard the [[USS Shreveport (LPD-12)|USS ''Shreveport'']], [[USS Estocin (FFG-15)|USS ''Estocin'']], [[USS Willamette (AO-180)|USS ''Willamette'']], and the [[USS Leyte Gulf (CG-55)|USS ''Leyte Gulf'']]\n\n==9-11 rescue efforts==\n[[File:David Thomas -- smithsonian uniform.jpg|thumb|The fire-damaged uniform Thomas was wearing on 9-11.]]\n\nCaptain David Thomas was serving in [[the Pentagon]] on [[September 11, 2001]], when [[al Qaeda]] [[Aircraft hijacking|hijackers]] crashed a passenger jet into it, causing an explosion, fire, and consequent injuries and loss of life.<ref name=MiamiHerald20080528/>\nThomas was one of the people who spontaneously volunteered to enter the damaged part of the building to rescue survivors.\n\nWhen asked about his rescue efforts on September 11, Thomas replied:\n\n{{quote|I am who I am, a trained sailor who sails ships at sea. You run toward your shipmate in times of trouble.}}\n\nHis fire-damaged uniform now hangs in the [[Smithsonian]]'s American History gallery.<ref name=MiamiHerald20080528/>\n\n==8th Commander of Joint Task Force Guantanamo==\n[[File:Mark Buzby hands over Guantanamo to David Thomas.jpg|thumb|[[Mark Buzby]] hands over [[Joint Task Force Guantanamo]] to David M. Thomas.]]\nOn May 27, 2008, [[Rear admiral (United States)|Rear Admiral]] David Thomas replaced Rear Admiral [[Mark Buzby]] to become the 8th Commander of [[Joint Task Force Guantanamo]], and the [[Guantanamo Bay detention camp]].<ref name=MiamiHerald20080528/>\n\nOn April 2, 2009, Thomas defended inviting visiting VIP entertainers to view detainees at Guantanamo.<ref name=MiamiHerald2009-04-02>\n{{cite news\n |url         = http://www.miamiherald.com/1218/story/981305.html\n |title       = Prison camps commander defends celebrity visits\n |publisher   = [[Miami Herald]]\n |author      = Carol Rosenberg\n |date        = 2009-04-02\n |accessdate  = 2009-04-02\n |archivedate = 2009-04-02\n |archiveurl  = https://www.webcitation.org/query?url=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.miamiherald.com%2F1218%2Fstory%2F981305.html&date=2009-04-02\n |url-status     = dead\n}}</ref>\n[[Miss Universe 2008]] [[Dayana Mendoza]] and \n[[Miss USA 2008]] [[Crystle Stewart]] had both been invited to visit Guantanamo on a [[USO]] tour, where they signed autographs.  Both women stirred controversy after they published accounts of their visits.  Thomas had authorized the women to view captives.<ref name=NYTimes2009-03-30>\n{{cite news\n |url         = http://thelede.blogs.nytimes.com/2009/03/30/miss-universe-visits-guantanamo/?hp\n |title       = Miss Universe Visits Guant\u00e1namo Bay\n |work=[[The New York Times]]\n |date        = 2009-03-30\n |author      = Robert Mackey\n |archiveurl  = https://www.webcitation.org/query?url=http%3A%2F%2Fthelede.blogs.nytimes.com%2F2009%2F03%2F30%2Fmiss-universe-visits-guantanamo%2F%3Fhp&date=2009-04-02\n |archivedate = 2009-04-02\n |accessdate  = 2009-04-02\n |url-status     = dead\n}}</ref><ref name=NYTimes2009-04-01>\n{{cite news\n |url         = http://thelede.blogs.nytimes.com/2009/04/01/miss-universes-blog-adds-to-guantanamo-debate/\n |title       = Miss Universe's Blog Post on Guant\u00e1namo Vanishes\n |work=The New York Times\n |date        = 2009-04-01\n |author      = Robert Mackey\n |archiveurl  = https://www.webcitation.org/query?url=http%3A%2F%2Fthelede.blogs.nytimes.com%2F2009%2F04%2F01%2Fmiss-universes-blog-adds-to-guantanamo-debate%2F&date=2009-04-02\n |archivedate = 2009-04-02\n |accessdate  = 2009-04-02\n |url-status     = dead\n}}</ref><ref name=TheTimes2009-04-01>\n{{cite news\n |url         = http://www.timesonline.co.uk/tol/comment/columnists/hugo_rifkind/article6024665.ece\n |title       = Life is lovely when you're wearing a tiara\n |publisher   = [[The Times]]\n |author      = Hugo Rifkind\n |date        = 2009-04-03\n |archiveurl  = https://www.webcitation.org/query?url=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.timesonline.co.uk%2Ftol%2Fcomment%2Fcolumnists%2Fhugo_rifkind%2Farticle6024665.ece&date=2009-04-02\n |archivedate = 2009-04-02\n |accessdate  = 2009-04-02\n |location    = London\n |url-status     = dead\n}}</ref><ref name=WashingtonPost2009-04-02>\n{{cite news\n |url         = https://www.washingtonpost.com/wp-dyn/content/article/2009/03/31/AR2009033103729.html?hpid=news-col-blog\n |title       = 'GWOT.' What Is It Good For? Absolutely Nothing!\n |publisher   = [[The Washington Post]]\n |author      = Al Kamen\n |date        = 2009-04-02\n |accessdate  = 2009-04-02\n |archivedate = 2009-04-02\n |archiveurl  = https://www.webcitation.org/query?url=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.washingtonpost.com%2Fwp-dyn%2Fcontent%2Farticle%2F2009%2F03%2F31%2FAR2009033103729.html%3Fhpid%3Dnews-col-blog&date=2009-04-02\n |url-status     = dead\n}}</ref><ref name=Independent2009-04-01>\n{{cite news\n |url         = http://www.independent.ie/opinion/columnists/ian-odoherty/bloody-wimmin-ruining-history-1694971.html\n |title       = Bloody Wimmin, ruining history\n |author      = Ian O'Doherty\n |publisher   = [[The Independent (Ireland)]]\n |date        = 2009-04-02\n |accessdate  = 2009-04-02\n |archivedate = 2009-04-02\n |archiveurl  = https://www.webcitation.org/query?url=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.independent.ie%2Fopinion%2Fcolumnists%2Fian-odoherty%2Fbloody-wimmin-ruining-history-1694971.html&date=2009-04-02\n |url-status     = dead\n}}</ref>\n[[Carol Rosenberg]], reporting in the ''[[Miami Herald]]'', wrote that Thomas \"brushed aside\" concerns that by allowing civilians to view the captives he was violating the clause in the Geneva Conventions that protect captives from the humiliation of public display.\n\nThomas asserted that the beauty queens had been allowed to view the detainees in Guantanamo just as if they were reporters.<ref name=MiamiHerald2009-04-02/>\n\n==Commander, Naval Surface Forces Atlantic==\n\nOn July 10, 2009, he began his assignment as commander, [[Carrier Strike Group Two|Carrier Strike Group 2]], serving in that capacity until July, 2010.  In July 2010, he was named Commander, Naval Surface Forces Atlantic (COMNAVSURFLANT), the senior Surface Warfare Officer (SWO) in the Atlantic Fleet, a position he held until September 4, 2013.<ref name=militarynews2013-09-04/>\n\n==BAE==\n\nAfter he left the Navy Thomas was hired as an executive at [[BAE]], a firm which builds and maintains large vessels, including [[US Navy]] vessels.<ref name=marinelink2018-02-09/>  In 2018 he was put in charge of BAE's [[San Diego, California|San Diego]] facility.<ref name=sdbj2018-09-09/>\n\n==References==\n<!-- \n| archivedate = | url-status = live | archiveurl =  \n| url-status = live | archivedate = | archiveurl =  \n| url-status = dead | archivedate = | archiveurl =  \n -->\n{{Reflist|refs= \n<ref name=sdbj2018-09-09>\n{{cite news\n| url         = https://www.sdbj.com/news/2018/sep/09/ship-shape/\n| title       = New Leader, Bigger Dry Dock Working at Shipyard\n| work        = [[San Diego Business Journal]]\n| author      = Brad Graves\n| date        = 2018-09-09\n| location    = [[San Diego, California]]\n| archiveurl  = https://web.archive.org/web/20180910034746/http://sdbj.com/news/2018/sep/09/ship-shape/\n| archivedate = 2018-09-10\n| accessdate  = 2020-01-16\n| url-status  = live\n| quote       = Eight months into his new assignment, Thomas said he isn\u2019t planning any changes in San Diego. However, there is evidence the yard will be dealing with a greater volume of work than it did under Thomas\u2019 predecessor.\n}}\n</ref>\n\n<ref name=militarynews2013-09-04>\n{{cite news     \n| url         = https://www.militarynews.com/norfolk-navy-flagship/news/top_stories/naval-surface-force-atlantic-holds-change-of-command/article_af680702-c614-5b46-a0b5-266309127475.html\n| title       = Naval Surface Force Atlantic holds change of command\n| work        = [[Military News]]\n| date        = 2013-09-04\n| location    = [[Norfolk, Virginia]]\n| archiveurl  = https://web.archive.org/web/20200118041404/https://www.militarynews.com/norfolk-navy-flagship/news/top_stories/naval-surface-force-atlantic-holds-change-of-command/article_af680702-c614-5b46-a0b5-266309127475.html\n| archivedate = 2020-01-18\n| accessdate  = 2020-01-16\n| url-status  = live\n| quote       = Rear Adm. Pete A. Gumataotao relieved Rear. Adm. David M. Thomas, Jr. as Commander, Naval Surface Force Atlantic (SURFLANT) during a ceremony at the Naval Support Activity Norfolk chapel, Aug. 29. \n}}\n</ref>\n\n<ref name=marinelink2018-02-09>\n{{cite news     \n| url         = https://www.marinelink.com/news/jacksonville-destination433819\n| title       = BAE Systems Jacksonville: Ship Repair's 'Destination of Choice'\n| work        = [[Marine Link]]\n| author      = Greg Trauthwein\n| date        = 2018-02-09\n| archiveurl  = https://web.archive.org/web/20200118041101/https://www.marinelink.com/news/jacksonville-destination433819\n| archivedate = 2020-01-18\n| accessdate  = 2020-01-16\n| url-status  = live\n| quote       = In fact, since Thomas took command of the yard in 2014 (*Note: David M. Thomas, Jr., was recently named to lead BAE ship repair yard in San Diego after three years as Vice President & General Manager, Southeast Shipyards, Ship Repair, BAE Systems in Jacksonville), he credits a change in people skills as one of the leading changes at the yard during his tenure.\n}}\n</ref>\n}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{commonscat-inline|David M. Thomas}}\n*[http://www.navy.mil/navydata/bios/navybio.asp?bioID=429 Official U.S. Navy Biography]\n* {{USNAVY|article=Rear Admiral David M. Thomas, Jr|url=http://www.navy.mil/navydata/bios/navybio.asp?bioID=429}}\n\n